div.p:
The attached letter from Eshkol to youThis letter, dated September 29, was delivered by the Israeli Embassy to the Department of State on October 5 and forwarded to the White House under cover of a memorandum from Executive Secretary Read to Rostow, also dated October 5. (Ibid., Special Head of State Correspondence File, Israel, 8/1/68–12/12/68) says, in effect:
—the UAR doesn’t want peace; please don’t get in bed with the Soviet Union on the Middle East;
—the Israelis are trying to do something with Jordan;
—please give us the Phantoms;
—may I come and see you in December in the course of my trip to Latin America?
